Thursday, 27 April 2017 marks the 23rd year of Democracy in South Africa, the national public holiday celebrates freedom and commemorated the first post-apartheid elections held on the day in 1994. Leaders of various South African political parties, religious leaders and anti-Zuma supporters are gathered in Caledonia stadium in Pretoria for the Freedom Movement rally against President Jacob Zuma. Nelson Mandela&#8217;s granddaughter, Ndileka Mandela is one of the many public figures who are set to speak at the rally. #FreedomMovement goals include Zuma to step down, protect constitution, stop state capture &amp; &quot;restore power to ppl&quot; #FreedomDay #sabcnews pic.twitter.com/P42oQKZ6oq &mdash; Sipho Stuurman (@Sipho_Stuurman) April 27, 2017 &nbsp; &nbsp; #ZumaMustFall @MmusiMaimane &quot;@Our_DA: The message is clear! #ZumaMustGo #FreedomMovement #FreedomDay pic.twitter.com/J9Y2vfjyJC&quot; &mdash; ALETTAHA (@ALETTAHA) April 27, 2017 &quot;@JacaNews: #FreedomDay Nelson Mandela&#39;s granddaughter Ndileka Mandela at the #FreedomMovement Rally in PTA. SM pic.twitter.com/qAiiohsV73&quot; &mdash; #ZumaMustFall (@ZumaMustFallZA) April 27, 2017 #FreedomDay Nelson Mandela&#39;s former PA Zelda la Grange at the #FreedomMovement Rally in PTA. SM pic.twitter.com/jgGJV4RK8I &mdash; Jacaranda News (@JacaNews) April 27, 2017 Zelda la Grange &#8211; &quot;Claim back our power&quot; #FreedomMovement #FreedomDay pic.twitter.com/z0cCIsAFDj &mdash; Abigail Javier (@AbigailJavier_) April 27, 2017 WATCH: The singing of the National Anthem #sabcnews #FreedomMovement pic.twitter.com/XsRwphZlrx &mdash; Tshepiso Moche (@tshepimoche) April 27, 2017 &nbsp; #FreedomMovement rally in Caledonia Stadium, Pretoria pic.twitter.com/T29mpeRmpm &mdash; Sikelelwa Mdingi (@SikiGeyaMdingi) April 27, 2017 Now singing the National anthem #FreedomMovement #FreedomDay pic.twitter.com/TKpYT88KJa &mdash; Abigail Javier (@AbigailJavier_) April 27, 2017 Leadership has arrived #FreedomMovement #FreedomDay